Functional aur Class Component me difference

Functional component ek normal JavaScript function hota hai jo JSX return karta hai. Class component ek class hoti hai jo React.Component ko extend karti hai. Pehle state aur lifecycle ke liye class component use hota tha, lekin ab hooks (useState, useEffect) ki wajah se functional component zyada use hote hain kyunki ye simple, readable aur easy hote hain



Props:-
Props ka mtlab Hote Hai React me "properties" Props Ki Help Se ham Ek component Se durse Component Me Data Bhje sakhte hai yha Le sakhte Hai Props ka use parent component se child component ko data pass karne ke liye hota hai. Props read-only hote hain, child component unhe change nahi kar sakta


Example:-
Parent Function :-
// Parent.js
import Child from "./Child";

function Parent() {
  return (
    <>
      <h1>Parent Component</h1>

      <Child 
        name="Harshu"
        age={22}
      />
    </>
  );
}

export default Parent;


CHild Component :-
// Child.js
function Child(props) {
  return (
    <>
      <h2>Name: {props.name}</h2>
      <h2>Age: {props.age}</h2>
    </>
  );
}

export default Child;

normally parent re-render hoga toh child bhi re-render hoga, chahe props ki value same hi kyu na ho.
function Parent() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>+</button>
      <Child name="Harshu" />
    </>
  );
}

ahan button click karne par Parent re-render hoga, aur Child bhi dubara chalega even though name="Harshu" same hai.

Agar child ko unnecessary re-render se bachana ho toh React.memo use karte hain:


Example:-


const Child = React.memo(function Child({ name }) {
  return <h1>{name}</h1>;
});

Ab child tabhi re-render hoga jab prop ki value change hogi.




/////Most:-
Ham Child Se parent Ko Value Bhj Sakhte Hai par Ham Change nahi kar sakhte bas value Bhje sakhte hai 



Exmple:-
// Parent
function Parent() {
  const [name, setName] = useState("Harshu");

  function changeName(newName) {
    setName(newName);
  }

  return <Child changeName={changeName} />;
}



// Child
function Child({ changeName }) {
  return (
    <button onClick={() => changeName("Harsh Thakur")}>
      Change
    </button>
  );
}



Par Ham yeh Nhai Kar sakhte hai 


